look for one for checking cyl compression, usually screws into the spark
plug hole, get one with a lock so the needle remains until you release
it.  get the kind that screws in and has a hose, a longish tip will help
get it started but not mandatory.

> types for testing different things.  Not sure which I need. When I
> looked on the drivers side front of the engine (front means front of
> the car) There was a lot of oil in the compartment and the spark plug
> is all oily.

that oily sprak plug is a tell tale sign that somehow oil is getting into
the cyl...hole in piston, bad rings, etc...

> Guess I gotta find a place to bring it in to be looked

